	<ouc:div label="bio" group="Everyone" button-text="Bio">
		<ouc:editor csspath="/_resources/ou/editor/crimson/wysiwyg.css" cssmenu="/_resources/ou/editor/crimson/styles.txt" wysiwyg-class="maincontent" />
<p>J. David Archibald, Professor Emeritus, Department of Biology, College of Sciences SDSU taught courses on mammals, macroevolution, biogeography, and vertebrate evolution for 34 years at SDSU and elsewhere. His research on the systematics and evolution of early mammals, biostratigraphy, faunal analysis, extinction, and evolutionary history was funded by grants from various organizations, most notably the National Science Foundation and the National Geographic Society.</p>
    </ouc:div>

	 <ouc:div label="education" group="Everyone" button-text="Education">
        <ouc:editor csspath="/_resources/ou/editor/crimson/wysiwyg.css" cssmenu="/_resources/ou/editor/crimson/styles.txt" wysiwyg-class="full-width"/>
<p>Ph.D. in Paleontology University of California, Berkeley, 1977 | B.A. in Geology Kent State University, Kent, Ohio, 1972</p>
    </ouc:div>

    <ouc:div label="specialization" group="Everyone" button-text="Areas of Specialization">
